node.text:
Trees live, they grow, and they eventually die but
their journey is far from over. For instance, this is a
175-year-old homestead black walnut tree that was
shedding large limbs and had become hazardous so the
homeowner contacted us to remove it. With the help of
John Rodius (featured here), we were able to cut and
remove this massive tree in under 2 days. The family's
memories will be forever preserved in the grains of this
wood as it transitions to its second life in the form of live
edge slabs and wood veneer.

By @gl_veneer
